nl_problem:
# Task: BitmaskGrouper
# Interface:
Class: Solution
Method: groupNums(self, arg1)

Given an array of integers `nums`, group the elements into the smallest number of groups such that each group contains elements whose bitwise AND is non-zero.
Return the groups as a list of lists. (If multiple groupings exist with the same minimum number, any one is acceptable).

Constraints:
- 1 <= nums.length <= 1000
- 0 <= nums[i] <= 10^9
lisp_spec:
(task
  (name "groupNums")
  (signature ( (nums list) ) (list list))
  (constraints
    (constraint "1 <= length(nums) <= 1000")
    (constraint "0 <= nums[i] <= 10^9")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Group the elements of an array into the smallest number of groups such that each group contains elements whose bitwise AND is non-zero.")
    (rule "Each element in a group must have a non-zero bitwise AND with every other element in the same group.")
    (return "A list of lists, where each inner list represents a group. If multiple valid groupings exist, any one is acceptable.")
  )
)
